It’s understood say the body was found on Sunday at the quarry commonly known as Oupa Fats by two boys. JOHANNESBURG – The body of a man has been discovered in Lenasia, in southern Johannesburg. It’s understood that the body was found on Sunday at the quarry commonly known as Oupa Fats by two boys. The police’s Kay Makhubela has appealed to anyone with information to come forward. “When the police arrived, paramedics were summoned. They certified him dead. So far the motive for the killing is unknown, but he was found with bruises and some head injuries. We’ve opened a case of murder.”